tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  37,81,"Noah was definitely one of My servants who believed and acted according to My obedience."
  37,90,"So they left him behind and went."
  37,94,"So the worshippers of these idols came rushing to him."
  37,100,"“O my Lord! Grant me a pious child who will be a means of help for me and a substitute for me from my people in the wilderness.”"